६.१.१९३|लिति|लिति ६.१.१९३|६.१.१९३ लिति
The acute accent falls on the syllable immediately preceding the affix that has an indicatory ल्।<br><br>Terms: accent-तिङ्

६.१.१९४|आदिर्णमुल्यन्यतरस्याम्|आदिर्णमुल्यन्यतरस्याम् ६.१.१९४|६.१.१९४ आदिर्णमुल्यन्यतरस्याम्
The first syllable may be optionally acute when the absolutive affix णमुल् follows.<br><br>Terms: accent

६.१.१९५|अचः कर्तृयकि|अचः कर्तृयकि ६.१.१९५|६.१.१९५ अचः कर्तृयकि
The roots which are exhibited in धातुपाठ with a final vowel, may be optionally have the acute on the first syllable, before the affixes of the Passive (यक्), when the sense of the verb is Reflexive.<br><br>Terms: accent

६.१.१९६|थलि च सेटीडन्तो वा|थलि च सेटीडन्तो वा ६.१.१९६|६.१.१९६ थलि च सेटीडन्तो वा
Before the ending थ of the Perfect, Second Person Singular, when this ending takes the augment इ ; the acute accent falls either on the first syllable, or on this इ , or on the personal ending.<br><br>Terms: accent-धातु

६.१.१९७|ञ्नित्यादिर्नित्यम्|ञ्नित्यादिर्नित्यम् ६.१.१९७|६.१.१९७ ञ्नित्यादिर्नित्यम्
Whatever is derived with an affix having an indicatory ञ् or न् , has the acute accent invariably on the first syllable.<br><br>Terms: accent-तिङ्

६.१.१९८|आमन्त्रितस्य च|आमन्त्रितस्य च ६.१.१९८|६.१.१९८ आमन्त्रितस्य च
The first syllable of a Vocative gets the acute accent.<br><br>Terms: accent

६.१.१९९|पथिमथोः सर्वनामस्थाने|पथिमथोः सर्वनामस्थाने ६.१.१९९|६.१.१९९ पथिमथोः सर्वनामस्थाने
The acute accent is on the first syllable of पथिन् and मथिन् when followed by a strong case-ending.<br><br>Terms: accent-विभक्ति

६.१.२००|अन्तश्च तवै युगपत्‌|अन्तश्च तवै युगपत्‌ ६.१.२००|६.१.२०० अन्तश्च तवै युगपत्‌
The Infinitive in तवै has the acute on the first syllable and on the last syllable at one and the same time.<br><br>Terms: accent-विभक्ति-words

६.१.२०१|क्षयो निवासे|क्षयो निवासे ६.१.२०१|६.१.२०१ क्षयो निवासे
The word क्षय has the acute on the first syllable and on the last syllable at one and the same time.<br><br>Terms: accent-word

६.१.२०२|जयः करणम्|जयः करणम् ६.१.२०२|६.१.२०२ जयः करणम्
The acute accent falls on the first syllable of जय , in the sense of 'whereby one attains victory'.<br><br>Terms: accent-word

६.१.२०३|वृषादीनां च|वृषादीनां च ६.१.२०३|६.१.२०३ वृषादीनां च
The words वृष etc. have the acute on the first syllable.<br><br>Terms: accent-word

६.१.२०४|संज्ञायामुपमानम्‌|संज्ञायामुपमानम्‌ ६.१.२०४|६.१.२०४ संज्ञायामुपमानम्‌
The acute accent falls on the first syllable of that word with which something is likened, provided that it is a name.<br><br>Terms: accent-word

