७.४.९४|दीर्घो लघोः|दीर्घो लघोः ७.४.९४|७.४.९४ दीर्घो लघोः
In the reduplicative syllable, a prosodially short vowel is lengthened in the reduplicated Aorist of the Causative when the vowel of the root is light and the root has not lost its end-vowel before the Causative णि।<br><br>Terms: Reduplicate

७.४.९५|अत्‌ स्मृदृत्वरप्रथम्रदस्तॄस्पशाम्|अत्‌ स्मृदृत्वरप्रथम्रदस्तॄस्पशाम् ७.४.९५|७.४.९५ अत्‌ स्मृदृत्वरप्रथम्रदस्तॄस्पशाम्
Short अ is substituted for the vowel of the reduplicate in the reduplicated Aorist of the Causative of the roots 1. स्मृ 2. दॄ 3. त्वर 4. प्रथ 5. म्रद 6. स्तॄ and 7. स्पश्।<br><br>Terms: Reduplicate

७.४.९६|विभाषा वेष्टिचेष्ट्योः|विभाषा वेष्टिचेष्ट्योः ७.४.९६|७.४.९६ विभाषा वेष्टिचेष्ट्योः
Short अ is optionally substituted for the vowel of the reduplicate in the reduplicated Aorist of the Causative of वेष्ट् and चेष्ट्।<br><br>Terms: Reduplicate

७.४.९७|ई च गणः|ई च गणः ७.४.९७|७.४.९७ ई च गणः
