८.१.८|वाक्यादेरामन्त्रितस्यासूयासम्मतिकोपकुत्सनभर्त्सनेषु|वाक्यादेरामन्त्रितस्यासूयासम्मतिकोपकुत्सनभर्त्सनेषु ८.१.८|८.१.८ वाक्यादेरामन्त्रितस्यासूयासम्मतिकोपकुत्सनभर्त्सनेषु
A Vocative, at the beginning of a sentence, is repeated, when envy, praise, anger, blame, or threat is meant by the speaker.<br><br>Terms: Doubling of Words

८.१.९|एकं बहुव्रीहिवत्‌|एकं बहुव्रीहिवत्‌ ८.१.९|८.१.९ एकं बहुव्रीहिवत्‌
When एक is repeated, it is treated like a member of a बहुव्रीहि समास ।<br><br>Terms: Doubling of Words

८.१.१०|आबाधे च|आबाधे च ८.१.१०|८.१.१० आबाधे च
A word is repeated and is treated like a member of a बहुव्रीहि समास when a mental distress over something is expressed.<br><br>Terms: Doubling of Words

८.१.११|कर्मधारयवत्‌ उत्तरेषु|कर्मधारयवत्‌ उत्तरेषु ८.१.११|८.१.११ कर्मधारयवत्‌ उत्तरेषु
In the following rules, the double-word is treated like a कर्मधारय समास ।<br><br>Terms: Doubling of Words

८.१.१२|प्रकारे गुणवचनस्य|प्रकारे गुणवचनस्य ८.१.१२|८.१.१२ प्रकारे गुणवचनस्य
An adjective is repeated, when it is meant to express that the said attribute belongs to a thing only to a limited degree and the double word is treated like a कर्मधारय समास ।<br><br>Terms: Doubling of Words

८.१.१३|अकृच्छ्रे प्रियसुखयोरन्यतरस्याम्|अकृच्छ्रे प्रियसुखयोरन्यतरस्याम् ८.१.१३|८.१.१३ अकृच्छ्रे प्रियसुखयोरन्यतरस्याम्
The words प्रिय and सुख are repeated optionally when they mean 'easily, without any difficulty'.<br><br>Terms: Doubling of Words

८.१.१४|यथास्वे यथायथम्|यथास्वे यथायथम् ८.१.१४|८.१.१४ यथास्वे यथायथम्
The word यथायथम् is irregularly formed in the sense of 'respectively, fitly, properly'.<br><br>Terms: Doubling of Words

८.१.१५|द्वन्द्वं रहस्यमर्यादावचनव्युत्क्रमणयज्ञपात्रप्रयोगाभिव्यक्तिषु|द्वन्द्वं रहस्यमर्यादावचनव्युत्क्रमणयज्ञपात्रप्रयोगाभिव्यक्तिषु ८.१.१५|८.१.१५ द्वन्द्वं रहस्यमर्यादावचनव्युत्क्रमणयज्ञपात्रप्रयोगाभिव्यक्तिषु
The word द्वन्द्वम् is irregularly formed in the sense of 'secret' and when it expresses a 'limit', 'a separation', 'employing in a sacrificial vessel' and 'manifestation'.<br><br>Terms: Doubling of Words

८.१.१६|पदस्य|पदस्य ८.१.१६|८.१.१६ पदस्य
Up to इडाया वा ८.३.५४, inclusive, should be always supplied in every subsequent sūtra the phrase 'of a word' or 'to the whole of a word'.<br><br>Terms: Doubling of Words

८.१.१७|पदात्‌|पदात्‌ ८.१.१७|८.१.१७ पदात्‌
Up to सगतिरपि तिङ् ८.१.६८, inclusive, should always be supplied the phrase 'after a पद'.<br><br>Terms: Doubling of Words

८.१.१८|अनुदात्तं सर्वमपादादौ|अनुदात्तं सर्वमपादादौ ८.१.१८|८.१.१८ अनुदात्तं सर्वमपादादौ
Up to (सामान्यवचनं) विभाषितं विशेषवचने (बहुवचनम्) ८.१.७४, inclusive, should always be supplied the phrase 'the whole is unaccented, if it does not stand at the beginning of the foot of a verse'.<br><br>Terms: अनुदात्त

८.१.१९|आमन्त्रितस्य च|आमन्त्रितस्य च ८.१.१९|८.१.१९ आमन्त्रितस्य च
All the syllables of the Vocative Case are unaccented when a word precedes them and they do not stand at the beginning of a hemistich.<br><br>Terms: अनुदात्त

८.१.२०|युष्मदस्मदोः षष्ठीचतुर्थीद्वितीयास्थयोर्वान्नावौ|युष्मदस्मदोः षष्ठीचतुर्थीद्वितीयास्थयोर्वान्नावौ ८.१.२०|८.१.२० युष्मदस्मदोः षष्ठीचतुर्थीद्वितीयास्थयोर्वान्नावौ
dual of युष्मद् and अस्मद् are substituted वाम and नौ respectively ।<br><br>Terms: सर्वनाम

८.१.२१|बहुवचने वस्नसौ|बहुवचने वस्नसौ ८.१.२१|८.१.२१ बहुवचने वस्नसौ
For (the Genitive 6th-Case, Dative -4th Case and Accusative -2nd case) plural of युष्मद् and अस्मद् are substituted वस् and नस् respectively (when a word precedes and these substitutes are अनुदात्त).<br><br>Terms: सर्वनाम

८.१.२२|तेमयावेकवचनस्य|तेमयावेकवचनस्य ८.१.२२|८.१.२२ तेमयावेकवचनस्य
For the Genitive 6th-Case and Dative -4th Case singular (of युष्मद् and अस्मद् are substituted) ते and मे respectively (when a word precedes and these substitutes are अनुदात्त).<br><br>Terms: सर्वनाम

८.१.२३|त्वामौ द्वितीयायाः|त्वामौ द्वितीयायाः ८.१.२३|८.१.२३ त्वामौ द्वितीयायाः
For the Accusative -2nd case singular of युष्मद् and अस्मद् are substituted त्वा and मा respectively (when a word precedes and these substitutes are अनुदात्त).<br><br>Terms: सर्वनाम

८.१.२४|न चवाहाहैवयुक्ते|न चवाहाहैवयुक्ते ८.१.२४|८.१.२४ न चवाहाहैवयुक्ते
when there is in connection with the सर्वनाम any of these - 1. च 'and' 2. वा 'or' 3. ह 'Oh!' 4. अह 'wonderful' or 5. एव 'only'.<br><br>Terms: सर्वनाम

८.१.२५|पश्यार्थैश्चानालोचने|पश्यार्थैश्चानालोचने ८.१.२५|८.१.२५ पश्यार्थैश्चानालोचने
The above substitutions do not take place also in connection with verbs having the sense of 'seeing' when physical seeing is not denoted.<br><br>Terms: सर्वनाम

८.१.२६|सपूर्वायाः प्रथमाया विभाषा|सपूर्वायाः प्रथमाया विभाषा ८.१.२६|८.१.२६ सपूर्वायाः प्रथमाया विभाषा
When the सर्वनाम follows a Nominative 1st-Case, which itself is preceded by another word, then the above substitutions may take place optionally.<br><br>Terms: सर्वनाम

८.१.२७|तिङो गोत्रादीनि कुत्सनाभीक्ष्ण्ययोः|तिङो गोत्रादीनि कुत्सनाभीक्ष्ण्ययोः ८.१.२७|८.१.२७ तिङो गोत्रादीनि कुत्सनाभीक्ष्ण्ययोः
The words गोत्र etc. become unaccented after a finite verb when a contempt or a repetition in intended.<br><br>Terms: सर्वनाम

८.१.२८|तिङ्ङतिङः|तिङ्ङतिङः ८.१.२८|८.१.२८ तिङ्ङतिङः
A finite verb is unaccented when a word precedes it which is not a finite verb.<br><br>Terms: Accent

८.१.२९|न लुट्|न लुट् ८.१.२९|८.१.२९ न लुट्
By the लुट् (Periphrastic Future) is not unaccented when it is preceded by a word which is not a finite verb.<br><br>Terms: Accent

८.१.३०|निपातैर्यद्यदिहन्तकुविन्नेच्चेच्चण्कच्चिद्यत्रयुक्तम्|निपातैर्यद्यदिहन्तकुविन्नेच्चेच्चण्कच्चिद्यत्रयुक्तम् ८.१.३०|८.१.३० निपातैर्यद्यदिहन्तकुविन्नेच्चेच्चण्कच्चिद्यत्रयुक्तम्
The finite verb retains its accent in connection with the particles 1. यत् 'that', 'because' 2. यदि 'if' 3. हन्त 'also', 'O!' 4. कुवित् 'well' 5. नेत् 'not' 6. चेत् 'if' 7. च 'if' 8. कच्चित् (interrogative particle implying 'I hope' or 'I hope not') and 9. यत्र 'where'. <br><br>Terms: Accent

८.१.३१|नह प्रत्यारम्भे|नह प्रत्यारम्भे ८.१.३१|८.१.३१ नह प्रत्यारम्भे
The finite verb retains its accent in connection with नह when used in the sense of forbidding.<br><br>Terms: Accent

८.१.३२|सत्यं प्रश्ने|सत्यं प्रश्ने ८.१.३२|८.१.३२ सत्यं प्रश्ने
The finite verb retains its accent in connection with सत्य when used in asking a question.<br><br>Terms: Accent

८.१.३३|अङ्गाप्रातिलोम्ये|अङ्गाप्रातिलोम्ये ८.१.३३|८.१.३३ अङ्गाप्रातिलोम्ये
The finite verb retains its accent in connection with अङ्ग when used in a friendly assertion.<br><br>Terms: Accent

८.१.३४|हि च|हि च ८.१.३४|८.१.३४ हि च
The finite verb retains its accent in connection with हि when used in a friendly assertion.<br><br>Terms: Accent

८.१.३५|छन्दस्यनेकमपि साकाङ्क्षम्‌|छन्दस्यनेकमपि साकाङ्क्षम्‌ ८.१.३५|८.१.३५ छन्दस्यनेकमपि साकाङ्क्षम्‌
In the छन्दस् (Vedas), the finite verb retains its accent (but not always) in connection with हि when it stands in correlation to another verb, even more than one.<br><br>Terms: Accent

८.१.३६|यावद्यथाभ्याम्|यावद्यथाभ्याम् ८.१.३६|८.१.३६ यावद्यथाभ्याम्
The finite verb retains its accent in connection with यावत् and यथा।<br><br>Terms: Accent

८.१.३७|पूजायां नानन्तरम्|पूजायां नानन्तरम् ८.१.३७|८.१.३७ पूजायां नानन्तरम्
But not so when these particles यावत् and यथा immediately precede the verb an denote 'praise'.<br><br>Terms: Accent

८.१.३८|उपसर्गव्यपेतं च|उपसर्गव्यपेतं च ८.१.३८|८.१.३८ उपसर्गव्यपेतं च
A finite verb loses its accent when it denotes 'praise' and is joined immediately with यावत् and यथा through the intervention of an उपसर्ग (verbal Preposition).<br><br>Terms: Accent

८.१.३९|तुपश्यपश्यताहैः पूजायाम्|तुपश्यपश्यताहैः पूजायाम् ८.१.३९|८.१.३९ तुपश्यपश्यताहैः पूजायाम्
The finite verb retains its accent in connection with 1. तु 2. पश्य 3. पश्यत and 4. अह when meaning 'praise'.<br><br>Terms: Accent

८.१.४०|अहो च|अहो च ८.१.४०|८.१.४० अहो च
The finite verb retains its accent in connection with अहो when meaning 'praise'.<br><br>Terms: Accent

८.१.४१|शेषे विभाषा|शेषे विभाषा ८.१.४१|८.१.४१ शेषे विभाषा
The finite verb optionally retains its accent in connection with अहो in the remaining cases (i.e. where it does not mean 'praise').<br><br>Terms: Accent

८.१.४२|पुरा च परीप्सायाम्|पुरा च परीप्सायाम् ८.१.४२|८.१.४२ पुरा च परीप्सायाम्
The finite verb optionally retains its accent in connection with पुरा when it means 'haste' (i.e. when पुरा means 'before').<br><br>Terms: Accent

८.१.४३|नन्वित्यनुज्ञैषणायाम्|नन्वित्यनुज्ञैषणायाम् ८.१.४३|८.१.४३ नन्वित्यनुज्ञैषणायाम्
The finite verb optionally retains its accent in connection with ननु when with this particle, permission is asked.<br><br>Terms: Accent

८.१.४४|किं क्रियाप्रश्नेऽनुपसर्गमप्रतिषिद्धम्‌|किं क्रियाप्रश्नेऽनुपसर्गमप्रतिषिद्धम्‌ ८.१.४४|८.१.४४ किं क्रियाप्रश्नेऽनुपसर्गमप्रतिषिद्धम्‌
The finite verb optionally retains its accent in connection with किम् when with this is asked a question relating to an action and when the verb is not preceded by a preposition or a negation.<br><br>Terms: Accent

८.१.४५|लोपे विभाषा|लोपे विभाषा ८.१.४५|८.१.४५ लोपे विभाषा
When however किम् is not added in asking such a question, the finite verb may optionally retain its accent.<br><br>Terms: Accent

८.१.४६|एहिमन्ये प्रहासे लृट्|एहिमन्ये प्रहासे लृट् ८.१.४६|८.१.४६ एहिमन्ये प्रहासे लृट्
In connection with एहिमन्ये used diversely in the लृट् (I Future) that follows it, retains its accent.<br><br>Terms: Accent

८.१.४७|जात्वपूर्वम्|जात्वपूर्वम् ८.१.४७|८.१.४७ जात्वपूर्वम्
The finite verb optionally retains its accent after जातु when this जातु is not preceded by another word.<br><br>Terms: Accent

८.१.४८|किम्वृत्तं च चिदुत्तरम्|किम्वृत्तं च चिदुत्तरम् ८.१.४८|८.१.४८ किम्वृत्तं च चिदुत्तरम्
Also after a form of किम् when the particle चित् follows it and when no other word precedes such form of किम् the finite verb retains its accent.<br><br>Terms: Accent

८.१.४९|आहो उताहो चानन्तरम्|आहो उताहो चानन्तरम् ८.१.४९|८.१.४९ आहो उताहो चानन्तरम्
Also after an immediately preceding आहो and उताहो when these follow, no other word, the verb retains its accent.<br><br>Terms: Accent

८.१.५०|शेषे विभाषा|शेषे विभाषा ८.१.५०|८.१.५० शेषे विभाषा
When the above mentioned particles आहो and उताहो do not immediately precede the verb, the verb may optionally retain its accent.<br><br>Terms: Accent

८.१.५१|गत्यर्थलोटा लृण्न चेत्‌ कारकं सर्वान्यत्‌|गत्यर्थलोटा लृण्न चेत्‌ कारकं सर्वान्यत्‌ ८.१.५१|८.१.५१ गत्यर्थलोटा लृण्न चेत्‌ कारकं सर्वान्यत्‌
The लृट् (I Future) retains its accent in connection with the Imperative of a verb denoting 'motion' ('to go', 'to come', 'to start' etc.) but only in that case, when the subject and object of both the verbs are not wholly different one from another.<br><br>Terms: Accent

८.१.५२|लोट् च|लोट् च ८.१.५२|८.१.५२ लोट् च
Also an लोट् (Imperative Mood), following after an Imperative of verbs of 'motion' retains its accent when the subject or object of both the verbs is not wholly different.<br><br>Terms: Accent

८.१.५३|विभाषितं सोपसर्गमनुत्तमम्‌|विभाषितं सोपसर्गमनुत्तमम्‌ ८.१.५३|८.१.५३ विभाषितं सोपसर्गमनुत्तमम्‌
An Imperative preceded by a preposition and not in the 1st person, following an Imperative of verbs of 'motion', may optionally retain its accent when the कारक is not wholly different.<br><br>Terms: Accent

८.१.५४|हन्त च|हन्त च ८.१.५४|८.१.५४ हन्त च
An Imperative with a preposition preceding it, may optionally retain its accent, in connection with हन्त , but not in the 1st person.<br><br>Terms: Accent

८.१.५५|आम एकान्तरमामन्त्रितमनन्तिके|आम एकान्तरमामन्त्रितमनन्तिके ८.१.५५|८.१.५५ आम एकान्तरमामन्त्रितमनन्तिके
After आम् , but separated from it by not more than one word, the Vocative retains its accent when the person addressed is not near.<br><br>Terms: Accent

८.१.५६|यद्धितुपरं छन्दसि|यद्धितुपरं छन्दसि ८.१.५६|८.१.५६ यद्धितुपरं छन्दसि
A finite verb followed by यत् or हि or तु retains its accent in the छन्दस् (Vedas).<br><br>Terms: Accent

८.१.५७|चनचिदिवगोत्रादितद्धिताम्रेडितेष्वगतेः|चनचिदिवगोत्रादितद्धिताम्रेडितेष्वगतेः ८.१.५७|८.१.५७ चनचिदिवगोत्रादितद्धिताम्रेडितेष्वगतेः
A finite verb retains its accent when it is not preceded by a गति Particle -- गतिश्च १.४.६० etc., and when it is followed by 1. चन 2. चिद् 3. इव 4. गोत्र etc., a तद्धित affix, or by its own doubled form.<br><br>Terms: Accent

८.१.५८|चादिषु च|चादिषु च ८.१.५८|८.१.५८ चादिषु च
A finite verb, not preceded by a गति , retains its accent before the particles च (1. वा 2. ह 3. अह and 4. एव -- न चवाहाहैवयुक्ते ८.१.२४).<br><br>Terms: Accent

८.१.५९|चवायोगे प्रथमा|चवायोगे प्रथमा ८.१.५९|८.१.५९ चवायोगे प्रथमा
The first finite verb only retains its accent in connection with च and वा।<br><br>Terms: Accent

८.१.६०|हेति क्षियायाम्|हेति क्षियायाम् ८.१.६०|८.१.६० हेति क्षियायाम्
In connection with ह , the first finite verb retains its accent when an offence against custom is reprimanded.<br><br>Terms: Accent

८.१.६१|अहेति विनियोगे च|अहेति विनियोगे च ८.१.६१|८.१.६१ अहेति विनियोगे च
In connection with अह , the first finite verb retains its accent when it refers to various commissions (as well as when a breach of good manners is condemned).<br><br>Terms: Accent

८.१.६२|चाहलोप एवेत्यवधारणम्|चाहलोप एवेत्यवधारणम् ८.१.६२|८.१.६२ चाहलोप एवेत्यवधारणम्
When च and अह are elided, the first finite verb still retains its accent when एव with the force of limitation, takes their place.<br><br>Terms: Accent

८.१.६३|चादिलोपे विभाषा|चादिलोपे विभाषा ८.१.६३|८.१.६३ चादिलोपे विभाषा
When च (1. वा 2. ह 3. अह and 4. एव -- न चवाहाहैवयुक्ते ८.१.२४) are elided the first verb optionally retains its accent.<br><br>Terms: Accent

८.१.६४|वैवावेति च च्छन्दसि|वैवावेति च च्छन्दसि ८.१.६४|८.१.६४ वैवावेति च च्छन्दसि
Also in connection with वै and वाव , may optionally, in the छन्दस् (Vedas), the first verb retains its accent.<br><br>Terms: Accent

८.१.६५|एकान्याभ्यां समर्थाभ्याम्|एकान्याभ्यां समर्थाभ्याम् ८.१.६५|८.१.६५ एकान्याभ्यां समर्थाभ्याम्
Also in connection with एक and अन्य , optionally in the छन्दस् (Vedas), the first verb retains its accent, when these word have the same meaning ('the one - the other').<br><br>Terms: Accent

८.१.६६|यद्वृत्तान्नित्यं|यद्वृत्तान्नित्यं ८.१.६६|८.१.६६ यद्वृत्तान्नित्यं
In connection with यद् in all its forms, the verb retains its accent always.<br><br>Terms: Accent

८.१.६७|पूजनात्‌ पूजितमनुदात्तम् (काष्ठादिभ्यः)|पूजनात्‌ पूजितमनुदात्तम् (काष्ठादिभ्यः) ८.१.६७|८.१.६७ पूजनात्‌ पूजितमनुदात्तम् (काष्ठादिभ्यः)
After a word denoting praise belonging to काष्ठादि class the word whose praise is denoted, becomes अनुदात्त ।<br><br>Terms: Accent

८.१.६८|सगतिरपि तिङ्|सगतिरपि तिङ् ८.१.६८|८.१.६८ सगतिरपि तिङ्
(After such words denoting praise) the finite verb (which is praised) becomes अनुदात्त even along with the गति , if any, that may precede it.<br><br>Terms: Accent

८.१.६९|कुत्सने च सुप्यगोत्रादौ|कुत्सने च सुप्यगोत्रादौ ८.१.६९|८.१.६९ कुत्सने च सुप्यगोत्रादौ
A finite verb along with its preceding गति , if any, become अनुदात्त when a noun denoting the fault of the action follows, with the exception of गोत्र etc.<br><br>Terms: Accent

८.१.७०|गतिर्गतौ|गतिर्गतौ ८.१.७०|८.१.७० गतिर्गतौ
A गति becomes unaccented when followed by another गति .<br><br>Terms: Accent

८.१.७१|तिङि चोदात्तवति|तिङि चोदात्तवति ८.१.७१|८.१.७१ तिङि चोदात्तवति
A गति becomes अनुदात्त when followed by an accented finite verb.<br><br>Terms: Accent

८.१.७२|आमन्त्रितं पूर्वम् अविद्यमानवत्‌|आमन्त्रितं पूर्वम् अविद्यमानवत्‌ ८.१.७२|८.१.७२ आमन्त्रितं पूर्वम् अविद्यमानवत्‌
A preceding Vocative is considered as non-existent (for the purposes of the accent of the following word and the enclitic forms of युष्मद् and अस्मद्).<br><br>Terms: Accent

८.१.७३|नामन्त्रिते समानाधिकरणे (सामान्यवचनम्)|नामन्त्रिते समानाधिकरणे (सामान्यवचनम्) ८.१.७३|८.१.७३ नामन्त्रिते समानाधिकरणे (सामान्यवचनम्)
A preceding Vocative, when it conveys a general idea, is not to be considered as if non-existent for the purposes of the subsequent Vocative, which stands in apposition with the former.<br><br>Terms: Accent

८.१.७४|विभाषितं विशेषवचने बहुवचनम्|विभाषितं विशेषवचने बहुवचनम् ८.१.७४|८.१.७४ विभाषितं विशेषवचने बहुवचनम्
When the preceding Vocative is in the plural number, it is optionally considered as non-existent, if the subsequent Vocative, in apposition with it, is a specific term.<br><br>Terms: Accent

८.२.१|पूर्वत्रासिद्धम्|पूर्वत्रासिद्धम् ८.२.१|८.२.१ पूर्वत्रासिद्धम्
Whatever will be taught hereafter, up to the end of the work, is to be considered as not taken effect, in relation to the application of a preceding rule.<br><br>Terms: असिद्ध

८.२.२|नलोपः सुप्स्वरसंज्ञातुग्विधिषु कृति|नलोपः सुप्स्वरसंज्ञातुग्विधिषु कृति ८.२.२|८.२.२ नलोपः सुप्स्वरसंज्ञातुग्विधिषु कृति
The elision of a final न् -- नलोपः प्रातिपदिकान्तस्य ८.२.७, is considered as if not to have taken effect, in applying the following rules - 1. rules regarding case-endings 2. rules regarding accents 3. rules regarding any technical term of Grammar and 4. rules regarding the augment त् before a कृत् affix.<br><br>Terms: असिद्ध

८.२.३|न मु ने|न मु ने ८.२.३|८.२.३ न मु ने
The sūtra अदसोऽसेर्दादु दो मः ८.२.८०, teaching the substitution of मु for the दस् of the pronoun अदस् is however not treated as असिद्ध in relation to the case-ending ना।<br><br>Terms: असिद्ध

८.२.४|उदात्तस्वरितयोर्यणः स्वरितोऽनुदात्तस्य|उदात्तस्वरितयोर्यणः स्वरितोऽनुदात्तस्य ८.२.४|८.२.४ उदात्तस्वरितयोर्यणः स्वरितोऽनुदात्तस्य
A स्वरित vowel is the substitute of an अनुदात्त vowel when the latter follows after such a semi-vowel which has replaced an उदात्त (acute accent) or a स्वरित vowel.<br><br>Terms: Accent

८.२.५|एकादेश उदात्तेनोदात्तः|एकादेश उदात्तेनोदात्तः ८.२.५|८.२.५ एकादेश उदात्तेनोदात्तः
The single substitute of an unaccented with an उदात्त (acute accent) vowel is उदात्त।<br><br>Terms: Accent

८.२.६|स्वरितो वाऽनुदात्ते पदादौ|स्वरितो वाऽनुदात्ते पदादौ ८.२.६|८.२.६ स्वरितो वाऽनुदात्ते पदादौ
The single substitute of an unaccented vowel standing at the beginning of a word, with an उदात्त (acute accent) vowel may optionally be a स्वरित or उदात्त (acute accent).<br><br>Terms: Accent

८.२.७|नलोपः प्रातिपदिकान्तस्य|नलोपः प्रातिपदिकान्तस्य ८.२.७|८.२.७ नलोपः प्रातिपदिकान्तस्य
The न् at the end of a nominal-stem, which is a पद -- शेषो घ्यसखि १.४.७, is elided.<br><br>Terms: Accent

८.२.८|न ङिसम्बुद्ध्योः|न ङिसम्बुद्ध्योः ८.२.८|८.२.८ न ङिसम्बुद्ध्योः
(But such न्) is not elided in the Locative -7th case and Vocative Case singular.<br><br>Terms: न् Elision

८.२.९|मादुपधायाश्च मतोर्वोऽयवादिभ्यः|मादुपधायाश्च मतोर्वोऽयवादिभ्यः ८.२.९|८.२.९ मादुपधायाश्च मतोर्वोऽयवादिभ्यः
For the म् of the affix मत् is substituted व if the अङ्ग (stem) ends in म् or अ ( and आ) or if these are in the penultimate position; but not after यव etc.<br><br>Terms: मतुप्

८.२.१०|झयः|झयः ८.२.१०|८.२.१० झयः
The व् is substituted for the म् of मत् after a अङ्ग (stem) ending in a mute consonant.<br><br>Terms: मतुप्

८.२.११|संज्ञायाम्|संज्ञायाम् ८.२.११|८.२.११ संज्ञायाम्
The व् is substituted for the म् of मत् when the word so formed is a Name.<br><br>Terms: मतुप्

८.२.१२|आसन्दीवदष्ठीवच्चक्रीवत्कक्षीवद्रुमण्वच्चर्मण्वती|आसन्दीवदष्ठीवच्चक्रीवत्कक्षीवद्रुमण्वच्चर्मण्वती ८.२.१२|८.२.१२ आसन्दीवदष्ठीवच्चक्रीवत्कक्षीवद्रुमण्वच्चर्मण्वती
The following names are irregularly formed 1. आसन्दीवत् 2. अष्ठीवत् 3. चक्रीवत् 4. कक्षीवत् 5. रुमण्वत् and 6. चर्मण्वती। (Reference श्लोक - आसन्दीवति धान्यादं रुक्मिणं हरितस्रजम्। अश्वं बबन्ध सारङ्गं देवेभ्यो अनमेजयः।)<br><br>Terms: मतुप्

८.२.१३|उदन्वानुदधौ च|उदन्वानुदधौ च ८.२.१३|८.२.१३ उदन्वानुदधौ च
The word उदन्वान् is irregularly formed in the sense of 'a sea'.<br><br>Terms: मतुप्

८.२.१४|राजन्वान् सौराज्ये|राजन्वान् सौराज्ये ८.२.१४|८.२.१४ राजन्वान् सौराज्ये
Also राजन्वान् when the sense is of a good government.<br><br>Terms: मतुप्

८.२.१५|छन्दसीरः|छन्दसीरः ८.२.१५|८.२.१५ छन्दसीरः
In the छन्दस् (Vedas) व् is substituted for the म् of मत् after a अङ्ग (stem) ending in इ (or ई) or र्।<br><br>Terms: मतुप्

८.२.१६|अनो नुट्|अनो नुट् ८.२.१६|८.२.१६ अनो नुट्
The affix मत् gets the augment नुट् in the छन्दस् (Vedas) after a अङ्ग (stem) ending in अन्।<br><br>Terms: नुट् augment

८.२.१७|नाद्घस्य|नाद्घस्य ८.२.१७|८.२.१७ नाद्घस्य
In the छन्दस् (Vedas) the affixes तर and तम get the augment नुट् after a stem in न्।<br><br>Terms: नुट् augment

८.२.१८|कृपो रो लः|कृपो रो लः ८.२.१८|८.२.१८ कृपो रो लः
For the र् of the root कृप् there is substituted ल्।<br><br>Terms: र् changed to ल्

८.२.१९|उपसर्गस्यायतौ|उपसर्गस्यायतौ ८.२.१९|८.२.१९ उपसर्गस्यायतौ
ल् is substituted for the र् of a preposition when अयते follows.<br><br>Terms: र् changed to ल्

८.२.२०|ग्रो यङि|ग्रो यङि ८.२.२०|८.२.२० ग्रो यङि
ल् is substituted for the र् of गॄ in the intensive.<br><br>Terms: र् changed to ल्

८.२.२१|अचि विभाषा|अचि विभाषा ८.२.२१|८.२.२१ अचि विभाषा
ल् is optionally changed to ल् before an affix beginning with a vowel.<br><br>Terms: र् changed to ल्

८.२.२२|परेश्च घाङ्कयोः|परेश्च घाङ्कयोः ८.२.२२|८.२.२२ परेश्च घाङ्कयोः
The र् of परि is changed to ल् before घ and अङ्क।<br><br>Terms: र् changed to ल्

८.२.२३|संयोगान्तस्य लोपः|संयोगान्तस्य लोपः ८.२.२३|८.२.२३ संयोगान्तस्य लोपः
When a word ends in a double consonant the last consonant is dropped.<br><br>Terms: र् changed to ल्

८.२.२४|रात्‌ सस्य|रात्‌ सस्य ८.२.२४|८.२.२४ रात्‌ सस्य
Of a word ending in a conjunct consonant, only स् is elided if it comes after र् (but any other consonant coming after र् is not elided).<br><br>Terms: स् changed to ल्

८.२.२५|धि च|धि च ८.२.२५|८.२.२५ धि च
The स् is elided before an affix beginning with ध।<br><br>Terms: स् Elision

८.२.२६|झलो झलि|झलो झलि ८.२.२६|८.२.२६ झलो झलि
The स् is elided when it is preceded by a झल् consonant (all consonant except semi-vowels and nasals) and is followed by an affix beginning with a झल् consonant.<br><br>Terms: स् Elision

८.२.२७|ह्रस्वादङ्गात्‌|ह्रस्वादङ्गात्‌ ८.२.२७|८.२.२७ ह्रस्वादङ्गात्‌
The स् is elided before an affix beginning with झल् consonant (all consonant except semi-vowels and nasals) when it is preceded by a अङ्ग (stem) ending in a short vowel.<br><br>Terms: स् Elision

८.२.२८|इट ईटि|इट ईटि ८.२.२८|८.२.२८ इट ईटि
The स् is elided after the augment इट् if after this स् the augment ईट् follows.<br><br>Terms: स् Elision

८.२.२९|स्कोः संयोगाद्योरन्ते च|स्कोः संयोगाद्योरन्ते च ८.२.२९|८.२.२९ स्कोः संयोगाद्योरन्ते च
The स् or क् , when initial in a conjunct consonant, are elided before a झल् (all consonant except semi-vowels and nasals) affix and at the end of a word.<br><br>Terms: Guttural

८.२.३०|चोः कुः|चोः कुः ८.२.३०|८.२.३० चोः कुः
A Guttural is substituted for a palatal before a झल् (all consonant except semi-vowels and nasals) affix or at the end of a word.<br><br>Terms: Guttural

८.२.३१|हो ढः|हो ढः ८.२.३१|८.२.३१ हो ढः
ढ is substituted for ह before a झल् (all consonant except semi-vowels and nasals) letter and at the end of a word.<br><br>Terms: ह changed to ढ

८.२.३२|दादेर्धातोर्घः|दादेर्धातोर्घः ८.२.३२|८.२.३२ दादेर्धातोर्घः
Of a root beginning with द , the ध is substituted for ह before a झल् (all consonant except semi-vowels and nasals) letter or at the end of a word.<br><br>Terms: ह changed to ध

८.२.३३|वा द्रुहमुहष्णुहष्णिहाम्|वा द्रुहमुहष्णुहष्णिहाम् ८.२.३३|८.२.३३ वा द्रुहमुहष्णुहष्णिहाम्
The ह of 1. द्रुह् 2. मुह् 3.ष्णुह् and 4. ष्णिह् is optionally changed to ध before a झल् (all consonant except semi-vowels and nasals) letter or at the end of a word.<br><br>Terms: ह changed to ध

८.२.३४|नहो धः|नहो धः ८.२.३४|८.२.३४ नहो धः
The ह of नह् is changed to ध before a before a झल् (all consonant except semi-vowels and nasals) letter or at the end of a word.<br><br>Terms: ह changed to ध

८.२.३५|आहस्थः|आहस्थः ८.२.३५|८.२.३५ आहस्थः
For the ह of the root आह् there is substituted थ before a झल् (all consonant except semi-vowels and nasals) letter.<br><br>Terms: ह changed to थ

८.२.३६|व्रश्चभ्रस्जसृजमृजयजराजभ्राजच्छशां षः|व्रश्चभ्रस्जसृजमृजयजराजभ्राजच्छशां षः ८.२.३६|८.२.३६ व्रश्चभ्रस्जसृजमृजयजराजभ्राजच्छशां षः
For the final consonants of 1. व्रश्च् 2. भ्रस्ज् 3. सृज् 4. मृज् 5. यज् 6. राज् and 7. भ्राज् and for the final छ and श , there is substituted ष् or at the end of a word.<br><br>Terms: Some substitution

८.२.३७|एकाचो बशो भष् झषन्तस्य स्ध्वोः|एकाचो बशो भष् झषन्तस्य स्ध्वोः ८.२.३७|८.२.३७ एकाचो बशो भष् झषन्तस्य स्ध्वोः
For the letters 1. ब 2. ग 3. ड or 4. द in the beginning of a mono-syllable and belonging to a root, and which ends in 1. झ 2. भ 3. घ 4. ढ or 5. ध there is substituted 1. भ 2. घ 3. ढ or 4. ध respectively before स् or ध्व or at the end of a word.<br><br>Terms: Some substitution

८.२.३८|दधस्तथोश्च|दधस्तथोश्च ८.२.३८|८.२.३८ दधस्तथोश्च
For the द of दध (the reduplicated form of धा) is substituted ध before the affixes beginning with त, थ, स and before ध्वम्।<br><br>Terms: Some substitution

८.२.३९|झलां जशोऽन्ते|झलां जशोऽन्ते ८.२.३९|८.२.३९ झलां जशोऽन्ते
A corresponding ज, ब, ग, ड or द is substituted for all consonants (with the exception of semi-vowels and nasals) at the end of a word.<br><br>Terms: हल् सन्धिः

